Juventus have reached an agreement to sign Barcelona midfielder Arthur at the end of the season. The Brazil international will join Juve for 72m euros (£66m) – with 10m (£9m) in add-ons. The 23-year-old, who joined Barcelona from Gremio on a six-year contract in 2018,has made 72 appearances for the Spanish champions. Juve’s 30-year-old Bosnia midfielder Miralem Pjanic will move in the opposite direction on a five-year deal. Pjanic will join Barcelona for 60m euros (£54.9m), with a further 5m (£4.6m) in add-ons. Juve are four points clear at the top of Serie A as they chase a ninth consecutive title.